#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="an3.163-182"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an3.163-182:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 3 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 3 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.163-182:0.2"
msgid "17. Kammapathapeyyāla "
msgstr "17. Courses of Deeds "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "an3.163-182:0.3"
msgid "163–182 "
msgstr "163–182 "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "an3.163-182:1.1"
msgid "“Tīhi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato yathābhataṃ nikkhitto evaṃ niraye. "
msgstr "“Someone with three qualities is cast down to hell. "

msgctxt "an3.163-182:1.2"
msgid "Katamehi tīhi? "
msgstr "What three? "

msgctxt "an3.163-182:1.3"
msgid "Attanā ca pāṇātipātī hoti, parañca pāṇātipāte samādapeti, pāṇātipāte ca samanuñño hoti. "
msgstr "They themselves kill living creatures. They encourage others to kill living creatures. And they approve of killing living creatures. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.163-182:1.4"
msgid "Imehi kho, bhikkhave, tīhi dhammehi samannāgato yathābhataṃ nikkhitto evaṃ niraye. "
msgstr "Someone with these three qualities is cast down to hell. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "an3.163-182:2.1"
msgid "Tīhi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato yathābhataṃ nikkhitto evaṃ sagge. "
msgstr "Someone with three qualities is raised up to heaven. "

msgctxt "an3.163-182:2.2"
msgid "Katamehi tīhi? "
msgstr "What three? "

msgctxt "an3.163-182:2.3"
msgid "Attanā ca pāṇātipātā paṭivirato hoti, parañca pāṇātipātā veramaṇiyā samādapeti, pāṇātipātā veramaṇiyā ca samanuñño hoti … pe …. (2) "
msgstr "They don’t themselves kill living creatures. They encourage others to not kill living creatures. And they approve of not killing living creatures. … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "an3.163-182:3.1"
msgid "Attanā ca adinnādāyī hoti, parañca adinnādāne samādapeti, adinnādāne ca samanuñño hoti … pe …. "
msgstr "They themselves steal. They encourage others to steal. And they approve of stealing. … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "an3.163-182:4.1"
msgid "Attanā ca adinnādānā paṭivirato hoti, parañca adinnādānā veramaṇiyā samādapeti, adinnādānā veramaṇiyā ca samanuñño hoti … pe …. (4) "
msgstr "They don’t themselves steal. They encourage others to not steal. And they approve of not stealing. … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli1.298, sc5
msgctxt "an3.163-182:5.1"
msgid "Attanā ca kāmesumicchācārī hoti, parañca kāmesumicchācāre samādapeti, kāmesumicchācāre ca samanuñño hoti … pe …. "
msgstr "They themselves commit sexual misconduct. They encourage others to commit sexual misconduct. And they approve of committing sexual misconduct. … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "an3.163-182:6.1"
msgid "Attanā ca kāmesumicchācārā paṭivirato hoti, parañca kāmesumicchācārā veramaṇiyā samādapeti, kāmesumicchācārā veramaṇiyā ca samanuñño hoti … pe …. (6) "
msgstr "They don’t themselves commit sexual misconduct. They encourage others to not commit sexual misconduct. And they approve of not committing sexual misconduct. … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc7
msgctxt "an3.163-182:7.1"
msgid "Attanā ca musāvādī hoti, parañca musāvāde samādapeti, musāvāde ca samanuñño hoti … pe …. "
msgstr "They themselves lie. They encourage others to lie. And they approve of lying. … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc8
msgctxt "an3.163-182:8.1"
msgid "Attanā ca musāvādā paṭivirato hoti, parañca musāvādā veramaṇiyā samādapeti, musāvādā veramaṇiyā ca samanuñño hoti … pe …. (8) "
msgstr "They don’t themselves lie. They encourage others to not lie. And they approve of not lying. … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc9
msgctxt "an3.163-182:9.1"
msgid "Attanā ca pisuṇavāco hoti, parañca pisuṇāya vācāya samādapeti, pisuṇāya vācāya ca samanuñño hoti … pe …. "
msgstr "They themselves speak divisively. They encourage others to speak divisively. And they approve of speaking divisively. … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc10
msgctxt "an3.163-182:10.1"
msgid "Attanā ca pisuṇāya vācāya paṭivirato hoti, parañca pisuṇāya vācāya veramaṇiyā samādapeti, pisuṇāya vācāya veramaṇiyā ca samanuñño hoti … pe …. (10) "
msgstr "They don’t themselves speak divisively. They encourage others to not speak divisively. And they approve of not speaking divisively. … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc11
msgctxt "an3.163-182:11.1"
msgid "Attanā ca pharusavāco hoti, parañca pharusāya vācāya samādapeti, pharusāya vācāya ca samanuñño hoti … pe …. "
msgstr "They themselves speak harshly. They encourage others to speak harshly. And they approve of speaking harshly. … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc12
msgctxt "an3.163-182:12.1"
msgid "Attanā ca pharusāya vācāya paṭivirato hoti, parañca pharusāya vācāya veramaṇiyā samādapeti, pharusāya vācāya veramaṇiyā ca samanuñño hoti … pe …. (12) "
msgstr "They don’t themselves speak harshly. They encourage others to not speak harshly. And they approve of not speaking harshly. … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc13
msgctxt "an3.163-182:13.1"
msgid "Attanā ca samphappalāpī hoti, parañca samphappalāpe samādapeti, samphappalāpe ca samanuñño hoti … pe …. "
msgstr "They themselves talk nonsense. They encourage others to talk nonsense. And they approve of talking nonsense. … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc14
msgctxt "an3.163-182:14.1"
msgid "Attanā ca samphappalāpā paṭivirato hoti, parañca samphappalāpā veramaṇiyā samādapeti, samphappalāpā veramaṇiyā ca samanuñño hoti … pe …. (14) "
msgstr "They don’t themselves talk nonsense. They encourage others to not talk nonsense. And they approve of not talking nonsense. … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc15
msgctxt "an3.163-182:15.1"
msgid "Attanā ca abhijjhālu hoti, parañca abhijjhāya samādapeti, abhijjhāya ca samanuñño hoti … pe …. "
msgstr "They themselves are covetous. They encourage others to be covetous. And they approve of covetousness. … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli1.299, sc16
msgctxt "an3.163-182:16.1"
msgid "Attanā ca anabhijjhālu hoti, parañca anabhijjhāya samādapeti, anabhijjhāya ca samanuñño hoti … pe …. (16) "
msgstr "They themselves are content. They encourage others to be contented. And they approve of being contented. … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc17
msgctxt "an3.163-182:17.1"
msgid "Attanā ca byāpannacitto hoti, parañca byāpāde samādapeti, byāpāde ca samanuñño hoti … pe …. "
msgstr "They themselves have ill will. They encourage others to have ill will. And they approve of having ill will. … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc18
msgctxt "an3.163-182:18.1"
msgid "Attanā ca abyāpannacitto hoti, parañca abyāpāde samādapeti, abyāpāde ca samanuñño hoti … pe …. (18) "
msgstr "They themselves are kind-hearted. They encourage others to be kind-hearted. And they approve of kind-heartedness. … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc19
msgctxt "an3.163-182:19.1"
msgid "Attanā ca micchādiṭṭhiko hoti, parañca micchādiṭṭhiyā samādapeti, micchādiṭṭhiyā ca samanuñño hoti … pe …. "
msgstr "They themselves have wrong view. They encourage others to have wrong view. And they approve of wrong view. … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc20
msgctxt "an3.163-182:20.1"
msgid "Attanā ca sammādiṭṭhiko hoti, parañca sammādiṭṭhiyā samādapeti, sammādiṭṭhiyā ca samanuñño hoti. "
msgstr "They themselves have right view. They encourage others to have right view. And they approve of right view. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.163-182:20.2"
msgid "Imehi kho, bhikkhave, tīhi dhammehi samannāgato yathābhataṃ nikkhitto evaṃ sagge”ti. (20) "
msgstr "Someone with these three qualities is raised up to heaven.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an3.163-182:20.3"
msgid "Kammapathapeyyālaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="uddanagatha"><p>
#. REF: sc21
msgctxt "an3.163-182:21.1"
msgid "Pāṇaṃ adinnamicchā ca, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.163-182:21.2"
msgid "musāvādī ca pisuṇā; "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.163-182:21.3"
msgid "Pharusā samphappalāpo ca, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.163-182:21.4"
msgid "abhijjhā byāpādadiṭṭhi ca; "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.163-182:21.5"
msgid "Kammapathesu peyyālaṃ, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.163-182:21.6"
msgid "tikakena niyojayeti. "
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p></blockquote></article></section></body></html>
